The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, May 10, 2004 				 Baits to beat the heat
																								The rising mercury has put tourism on a roll this summer and, with Olympic fever catching on, there are a host of offers and contests to beat the heat. Here are two exciting deals that are doing the rounds.																								Tourism Malaysia, in association with Singapore Airlines and five major travel agencies  SOTC, Cox amp; Kings, Thomas Cook, Travel Corporation and JTB Travels of India  have jointly introduced Malaysian Summer Dhamaka, an attractive summer package where the travellers get to spend two nights each in Kuala Lumpur and Penang.																								The package is priced at Rs 23,999 on a twin-sharing basis, with a discount of Rs 1,000 for Calcutta travellers.																								It will include airfares, accommodation with breakfast, seat in coach basis, airport transfers and bus transfers between Penang and Kuala Lumpur along with a half-day site seeing at these places.																								The package is valid till June 30 and will be available from New Delhi, Mumbai, Bangalore, Chennai and Calcutta.Catch the Olympic fever!																								Five lucky Visa credit and debit cardholders stand to win an all-expenses paid trip for two to the Olympic Games 2004 in Athens. Through this exciting offer, Visa, the worldwide sponsor of the Athens 2004 Olympic Games, extends its association with the Olympic Games to its cardholders in India along with the programme partner Samsung, the official wireless communications sponsor for the Olympics 2004.																								Every time a Visa cardholder in the cities of New Delhi, Mumbai, Calcutta, Bangalore and Hyderabad use their cards at shops, restaurants, supermarkets and other Visa merchant accepting locations, and spend a minimum of Rs 300, they become eligible to participate in this offer.																								They just need to swipe their card, dial in the contest number and answer a simple question to make them eligible for a draw. 					 CHANDRALEKHA TULAL
